The General Overseer, King Jesus Palace Miracles Min­istries (KJPMM), aka ‘Solu­tion Ground’, Bishop David Eichie, has said that only honesty on the path of lead­ers can check insecurity in the country. Speaking exclusively with Sunday INDEPEN­DENT on Saturday at the KJPMM headquarters along Akute/ Ajuwon road, Ogun State, Eichie decried the spate of insecurity in the country, stressing that it was worrisome, as it had become difficult for citizens to travel within Nigeria at the moment. “Leaders must rise. They must call a spade, a spade in terms of dealing with all known trouble makers or groups operating like terrorists, irrespective of creed, tribe and affiliations. IPOB Allays Fears Of Lockdown In South-East, Announces… Obi Cubana’s NDLEA Invitation, Another Ethnic Harassment –Kalu “We have to be honest with ourselves to tackle the current security challeng­es, what has kept us where we are today is dishonesty to ourselves. “We do not speak the truth to ourselves and you know the scripture says it is only the truth can set one free. “If we need to be free from the oppression of the terrorists to put all people and groups disturbing and terrorising the peace of the country together; our lead­ers must come together and tell themselves the truth,” he said.